> I think pub should be improved to support packages with domain - name prefixes (the domain name needs to be authenticated). There are always cases where package names are occupied. For example, dev.flutter.material. [@Piinks](https://github.com/Piinks)

@lwj1994 
your suggestion could be a feature request [HERE](https://github.com/dart-lang/pub-dev/issues)

For what it's worth, I have a similar problem and I have a temporary solution / a fix inspiration.

My problem:
* I switched to xcode 12 / ios 14
* then, when I clicked on my app's "find picture" button, I just get a full white screen (on a simulator)
* of course, everything was fine with xcode 11

My temporary solution is to use another package:
* I tried **[file_picker]** by @miguelpruivo, but the same error happened
* I tried **[multi_image_picker]** by @Sh1d0w, and everything worked OK

**[multi_image_picker]** - though successful - is not my target package because I only need one image and the potential multiple image choice brings confusion to the end-user, but that's good enough for the moment.
And I assume that you guys that develop **[image_picker]** may find inspiration in that code.
The only settings difference is uncommenting the `platform` line in `Podfile`
```
# Uncomment this line to define a global platform for your project
# platform :ios, '9.0'
```

[Edit] Additional info about versions and basic code during my tests
```
multi_image_picker: ^4.7.14
file_picker: ^2.0.0
image_picker: ^0.6.7+8
```

```dart
// file_picker version
final FilePickerResult result = await FilePicker.platform.pickFiles(type: FileType.image);
final PlatformFile platformFile = result.files.first;
// ...

// image_picker version
final picker = ImagePicker();
final pickedFile = await picker.getImage(source: ImageSource.gallery);
final File inputFile = File(pickedFile.path);
// ...

// multi_image_picker version
try {
  final List<Asset> resultList = await MultiImagePicker.pickImages(maxImages: 1);
  if (resultList == null || resultList.length != 1) {
    return false;
  }
  final Asset asset = resultList[0];
  // ....
} on Exception catch (e) {
  // ....
}
```

@monsieurtanuki with a single pick, if you wait a bit (depending of how many pictures do you have) they will appear. This happens only on the first time.

Would you mind to let it stay on the white screen (modal) for a while until something shows up?

iOS now allows you to access pictures without permissions if you don’t do anything intrusive with them. This is, for read only from what I’ve understood.

@miguelpruivo OK, I've just tried again with the single pick mode. I've had crash in the logs (as before), and after one minute still the same white screen...
And we're talking about an empty simulator with 6 default pictures, that load immediately in the multi pick mode (but after the modal "allow?" dialog).
It's good news if iOS now allows access to pictures without permissions for read-only access. A bit like what [Android already does, sometimes](https://github.com/miguelpruivo/flutter_file_picker/issues/289).

@monsieurtanuki with `allowMultiple` set to `false` you shouldn't require any permission as it uses native picker with read only permissions (introduced with iOS 14). 

Answering your question, currently not. I'm trying to detach as much as possible of 3rd party libraries and having all native and clean, to prevent dependency issues (or maintenance as well). If I could, I'd have the native picker for single and multi, but it isn't supported.

I'm sorry, but I'm having a hard time in understanding what actually is triggering an issue (crash) for you. So basically, it only crashes with multi pick, am I correct?

@miguelpruivo The problem seems to be precisely with the new "native picker with read only permissions (introduced with iOS 14)".
Multi file is OK - I mean - I have the "allow" dialog and I can see and pick files. I could use it: the problem is that I only want one file - and I cannot ask the end-user to understand that I ask him only one file though the interface allows him to select 0-n files. Very poor UX.
Single file pick does NOT work in my demo sample.

@monsieurtanuki I've just published [file_picker 2.0.1](https://pub.dev/packages/file_picker/changelog#201) with support for new iOS 14 API, you should be able to pick single and multi seamless now with same native UI. On iOS 13 or below the behavior is unchanged. Let me know if it worked for you.

@JJCrystalForest you can also fix it by using [file_picker 2.0.1](https://pub.dev/packages/file_picker/changelog#201).

Thank you!
